problem_prompt: Solve the following problem. What is the greatest number of Sundays that can occur in the first $49$ days of a year?
solution: 49 days is seven full weeks, so there are always $\boxed{7}$ Sundays.
gpt_response: Since each week has $7$ days and any day of the week can be the first day of a year, the maximum number of Sundays that can occur in the first $49$ days of a year is $\boxed{7}$.
